The paper deals with the problem of estimating the parameters of negative mixture models, which is a topic in machine learning and statistics. The paper proposes a method based on tensor decompositions, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and signal processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the use of probabilistic automata, which falls under the sub-category cs.SD (Systems and Control), and the use of tensor power method, which falls under the sub-category cs.IT (Information Theory).
